name: Break-up Advice - Humorous Greeting Card
description: A humorous card designed to make your best friend chuckle. It measures 5.5 X 8.5”, blank on the inside, and comes with a white envelope. In case the print is hard to read on your computer screen, the card says: Some advice for my best friend. If you’re dating a guy at the office named Max and you need to break up with him, here is a song to help you out: Hit the road, Max and don’t you fax me no more, no more. Hit the road, Max and don’t you fax me no more. On the other hand, if you need to break up with a guy named Chuck, I have a slightly different song. Let me know. Copyright 2007 Kristine Vangeloff

name: Bye, Bye, Larry - Humorous Greeting Card
description: Fun card to send to a friend that shares your evil, whacky sense of humor. Inside is blank for your message. The card is 5.5 X 8.5” and comes with a white envelope. It’s printed on card stock with an ink jet printer. Hope it made you smile. PS – If the text is difficult to read on your computer screen, the card says: I wanted to break up with my boyfriend, Larry, but Larry is the needy type and I knew I wouldn’t want to listen to all the whining and crying. Finally, I just shoved him into the bottom of my china cabinet and sealed the whole thing with collage paper and Mod Podge. I don’t think Larry is getting out any time soon. So, what’s new with you? Copyright 2007 Kristine Vangeloff

name: Strings Attached - Humorous Greeting Card
description: A fun card to send to a friend who shares your sense of humor. It’s blank inside so you can add whatever message you’d like. The card is 5.5 X 8.5”, printed on card stock with an ink jet printer. White envelope included. Copyright 2007 Kristine Vangeloff

name: Rolling Stones Lyrics Greeting Card
description: If you have a friend that’s a big rock ‘n roll fan, no other explanation is needed. They’ll totally get it. This card was designed by me using copyright-free images. It measures 5.5 X 8.5” and is printed on card stock. It comes with a white envelope. Hope you enjoy it. Copyright 2007 Kristine Vangeloff and freegirlystuff.com
